Suntech Earnings Spike After Realizing Gains From Solar Fund

-- B y   W i l l   W a d e
-- 
2011-03-08T22:24:43Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-08/suntech-earnings-spike-after-realizing-gains-from-solar-fund.html
Suntech Power Holdings Co., the
world’s largest maker of solar panels, reported today net income
of $383.4 million, or $2.02 an American depositary receipt, for
the fourth quarter.  Analysts had expected earnings of 29 cents, the average of
19 estimates compiled by Bloomberg.  Suntech reported net income of $33.1 million, or 18 cents
an ADR, in the third quarter.  The Wuxi, China-based company invests in the Global Solar
Fund, which provides funding to energy project developers.
“GSF’s fair value substantially increased and Suntech realized
equity income of $250 million in the fourth quarter of 2010,”
the company said in a statement.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Will Wade at 
 wwade4@bloomberg.net  